# Server-spezifische Test-Patterns

> Detail-Referenz — geladen aus `TESTING.md` Index.

## Environment-Variable-Snapshot

Tests die `process.env` manipulieren, müssen den Originalzustand wiederherstellen:

```typescript
test("uses custom API key from env", async () => {
  const originalEnv = { ...process.env }
  try {
    process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY = "test-key-123"

    const result = await createClient()

    expect(result.apiKey).toBe("test-key-123")
  } finally {
    process.env = originalEnv
  }
}
```

### Alternativ mit `beforeEach`/`afterEach`

```typescript
describe("API Client", () => {
  const originalEnv = { ...process.env }

  afterEach(() => {
    process.env = { ...originalEnv }
  })

  test("falls back to default when key missing", async () => {
    delete process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY
    await expect(createClient()).rejects.toThrow(/API key/i)
  })
})
```

## Fetch-Mock mit Cleanup

```typescript
describe("AdjustmentAssistant", () => {
  const originalFetch = globalThis.fetch

  afterEach(() => {
    globalThis.fetch = originalFetch
  })

  test("sends structured request to provider", async () => {
    globalThis.fetch = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(
      new Response(JSON.stringify({ choices: [{ message: { content: "result" } }] })),
    )

    const result = await assistant.process("input")

    expect(result).toBe("result")
  })
})
```

## Async-Testing

Vitest unterstützt async Tests nativ — kein spezielles Plugin nötig:

```typescript
// Async-Ergebnis prüfen
test("compiles rules asynchronously", async () => {
  const rules = await compileRules(draftRules)
  expect(rules).toHaveLength(3)
})

// Async-Fehler prüfen
test("rejects invalid rule format", async () => {
  await expect(compileRules(invalidInput)).rejects.toThrow(/invalid selector/i)
})
```

## Zod-Schema-Validierung testen

Teste Validierung mit echten Zod-Schemas, nicht Mocks:

```typescript
import { DraftRuleSchema } from "@chat-exporter/shared"

test("rejects rule without selector", () => {
  const result = DraftRuleSchema.safeParse({ effect: { type: "replace", value: "x" } })

  expect(result.success).toBe(false)
  expect(result.error?.issues[0].path).toContain("selector")
})

test.each(["heading", "paragraph", "code-block"])("accepts valid selector type: %s", (type) => {
  const result = DraftRuleSchema.safeParse({
    selector: { type, value: "test" },
    effect: { type: "replace", value: "changed" },
  })

  expect(result.success).toBe(true)
})
```

## Test-Imports

Server-Tests importieren Vitest-Globals explizit:

```typescript
import { describe, expect, test } from "vitest"
import type { AdjustmentSelection } from "@chat-exporter/shared"
```

## Testdatei-Platzierung

Tests liegen **neben dem Quellcode** (co-located):

```
apps/server/src/lib/
├── adjustment-preview.ts
├── adjustment-preview.test.ts
├── adjustment-assistant.ts
└── adjustment-assistant.test.ts
```

